  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sanitization for Covid-19 Reaching Underserved Beneficiaries (SCRUB)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Sanitization for Covid-19 Reaching Underserved Beneficiaries (SCRUB) Project will provide target 90,000 individuals (including 25,200 men, 25,200 women, 19,800 boys and 19,800 girls with WASH assistance in Homs and Rural Damascus to reduce the spread of COVID-19 in Syria. ADRA will provide monthly supplies of hygiene kits to 10,000 families (50,000 individuals) who are part of ADRA&#x2019;s food voucher program funded by USAID (Food For Peace) for three months. ADRA will also rehabilitate the WASH facilities in four health facilities in the target areas for hygiene kit distribution, increasing community resilience, with an estimated 40,000 beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
